Ciompi Revolt - Wikipedia|https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ciompi_Revolt|Ciompi Revolt ([[ˈt͡ʃom.pi]], CHOM-pee; Italian: Tumulto dei Ciompi) was a rebellion among unrepresented labourers which occurred in the Republic of Florence in Tuscany, Italy, from 1378 to 1382.: 201 Those who revolted consisted of artisans, labourers, and craftsmen who did  ...    the government beginning in 1378.: 67 In becoming the ciompi, the word derives from the florentine word for ‘cardare la lana’ or ‘ciompare’ as the wool workers were the most representative and numerous group of people involved in the  ...    The Revolt of the Ciompi was a popular revolt in Florence in 1378 spearheaded by wool carders known as Ciompi (Italian pronunciation: [[ˈtʃompi]]) and other non-guilded workers who rose up to demand a  ...    Coat of arms of the Arte della Lana
